## 1. What is Cloud Computing with example?
Cloud computing is the on-demand delivery of IT resources-such as servers, storage, databases, networking, software, and analytics-over the internet, allowing users to access and use these resources without owning or managing physical infrastructure. For example, using Google Drive to store and share files online is a form of cloud computing[88][91][92].

## 2. Who is the father of cloud computing?
Dr. Joseph Carl Robnett Licklider is widely regarded as the "father of cloud computing" for his pioneering work on ARPANET, which laid the foundation for network-based computing.

## 3. List down the basic characteristics of cloud computing
- On-demand self-service
- Broad network access
- Resource pooling
- Rapid elasticity
- Measured service[89]

## 4. What do you mean by Vertical and Horizontal scaling in Cloud Computing?
- Vertical scaling: Increasing the capacity of a single server (e.g., adding more RAM or CPU).
- Horizontal scaling: Adding more servers to distribute the load and increase capacity.

## 5. What are the services provided by Cloud Computing?
- Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS)
- Platform as a Service (PaaS)
- Software as a Service (SaaS)[85][88][91][92]

## 6. What are different models in Deployment in Cloud Computing?
- Public cloud
- Private cloud
- Hybrid cloud[89]

## 7. Mention the platforms used for Large Scale Cloud Computing
- Amazon Web Services (AWS)
- Microsoft Azure
- Google Cloud Platform (GCP)

## 8. Mention the name of some large cloud providers and databases
- Providers: AWS, Microsoft Azure, Google Cloud, IBM Cloud
- Databases: Amazon RDS, Google Cloud SQL, Azure SQL Database

## 9. Explain the difference between cloud and traditional datacenters

| Aspect           | Cloud Computing                | Traditional Datacenter       |
|------------------|-------------------------------|-----------------------------|
| Ownership        | Third-party provider           | Owned by organization       |
| Scalability      | Highly scalable on demand      | Limited, manual scaling     |
| Cost             | Pay-as-you-go                  | High upfront investment     |
| Maintenance      | Provider-managed               | Organization-managed        |

## 10. What are the different components required in cloud computing?
- Frontend platform (client devices)
- Backend platform (servers, storage)
- Network
- Cloud-based delivery[84]

## 11. What are the different platforms of cloud architecture?
- AWS, Azure, Google Cloud Platform, IBM Cloud, Oracle Cloud

## 12. What is a cloud service?
A cloud service is any computing resource (infrastructure, platform, or software) delivered over the internet and managed by a third-party provider[85][86][87][88].

## 13. List down the basic clouds in cloud computing
- Public cloud
- Private cloud
- Hybrid cloud

## 14. What are some issues with Cloud Computing?
- Security and privacy concerns
- Downtime and outages
- Compliance and legal issues
- Limited control and flexibility

## 15. Mention the services provided by Windows Azure Operating System
- Virtual machines
- App services
- SQL databases
- Storage
- Networking[91]

## 16. What is Cloud Computing Architecture?
Cloud computing architecture is the combination of components and subcomponents required for cloud computing, including frontend and backend platforms, a network, and cloud-based delivery[84][83].

## 17. What are the Services provided by AWS?
- Compute (EC2)
- Storage (S3)
- Databases (RDS, DynamoDB)
- Networking (VPC)
- AI/ML, Analytics, Security, and more[88]

## 18. What are the Services provided by Microsoft?
- Azure Virtual Machines
- Azure App Services
- Azure SQL Database
- Azure Storage
- Azure AI and analytics[91]

## 19. What is Virtualization?
Virtualization is the creation of virtual versions of resources (servers, storage, networks) to maximize hardware utilization and flexibility.

## 20. What is an EC2 instance?
An EC2 instance is a virtual server in Amazon's Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) for running applications on AWS[88].

## 21. What is AMI in EC2?
AMI (Amazon Machine Image) is a template that contains the software configuration (OS, application server, applications) required to launch an EC2 instance.

## 22. How to launch an on-demand EC2 instance in AWS?
- Log in to AWS Console
- Go to EC2 Dashboard
- Click "Launch Instance"
- Choose an AMI
- Select instance type
- Configure instance details
- Add storage
- Configure security group
- Launch instance

## 23. What is Google App Engine?
Google App Engine is a Platform as a Service (PaaS) that lets you build and host applications on Google’s infrastructure.

## 24. What are advantages of Google App Engine?
- Automatic scaling
- Managed infrastructure
- Supports multiple languages
- Integrated with Google Cloud services

## 25. What are the steps to install and configure Google App Engine?
- Install Google Cloud SDK
- Initialize SDK and authenticate
- Create a project in Google Cloud Console
- Deploy your application using the SDK

## 26. What is Apex?
Apex is a strongly typed, object-oriented programming language used for developing applications on the Salesforce platform.

## 27. What are the Features of Apex as language?
- Strongly typed
- Object-oriented
- Built-in support for DML operations
- Triggers and classes

## 28. What are the application of Apex?
- Automating business processes in Salesforce
- Customizing Salesforce applications
- Integrating with external systems

## 29. List some Apex Code Development Tools?
- Salesforce Developer Console
- Visual Studio Code with Salesforce extensions
- Eclipse with Force.com IDE

## 30. What are the steps to create application using Apex Programming Language?
- Create a Salesforce Developer account
- Write Apex classes/triggers
- Test and debug code
- Deploy to production

## 31. What is Salesforce.com Inc.?
Salesforce.com Inc. is a leading cloud-based software company specializing in CRM (Customer Relationship Management) solutions.

## 32. What is Lightning Platform?
Lightning Platform is Salesforce’s platform-as-a-service (PaaS) for building and deploying cloud applications.

## 33. How to create Custom Application using Salesforce Classic?
- Go to Setup
- Click "Create" > "Apps"
- Click "New" and follow the wizard to define your app

## 34. What is the difference between custom application and console application in Salesforce?

| Type                  | Custom Application           | Console Application           |
|-----------------------|-----------------------------|------------------------------|
| Purpose               | General business processes  | High-volume service/sales    |
| UI                    | Standard tabs and pages     | Multi-tab workspace          |

## 35. What are the steps to create custom application using Salesforce?
- Go to Setup
- Navigate to Apps
- Click "New"
- Define app details and add tabs
- Assign to user profiles

## 36. What is hypervisor in Cloud Computing?
A hypervisor is software that creates and manages virtual machines by abstracting hardware resources.

## 37. Explain Load Balancing in Cloud Computing.
Load balancing distributes incoming network traffic across multiple servers to ensure reliability and optimal resource use.

## 38. List the open-source cloud computing platform databases
- MySQL
- PostgreSQL
- MongoDB
- Cassandra

## 39. What are recent trends of Cloud Computing?
- Serverless computing
- Edge computing
- AI/ML integration
- Multi-cloud strategies

## 40. Applications of Cloud Computing
- Web hosting
- Data storage and backup
- Big data analytics
- Disaster recovery
- Internet of Things (IoT)
- Software development and testing

